column4: Activate New  - Used to activate a members Vitality membership.

Activate Exisiting - If a party already exists for the person for which a Vitality membership activation is requested. Vitality can re-use the existing party and create a new membership for that party where the party have membership in the past
Cancel Inception - Used to end date a members Vitality Membership to the start date of the membership.
Create - Used to update a party details. An example of party update would be updates to the Party?s name.
Create Role - Used to create a new membership role
Delete Role - Used to delete the membership role
Extend - Used to extend a members Vitality membership beyond the current date.
Update Product - Used to update the membership product
Update Role - Updates the membership party role
Update Start Date - Used to update the Vitality Membership details.
